               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671028-name-163" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18671028-name-163" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671028-name-163" type="surname" value="LINDSEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18671028-name-163" type="given" value="EDWIN CHARLES"></interp>EDWIN CHARLES LINDSEY.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a carman, of 52, Maria Street, Kings<lb></lb>land Road—on 24th October, about nine p.m., I was in Commercial Street and was tripped up by three or four men—the prisoner is one, I saw him pick my money up off the pavement—I had 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., some in a purse and some loose; it was taken out of my left trousers pocket before I was forced on the ground—they ran away—I called, "Police! "and as soon as I got up an officer had the prisoner; I am sure he is lone of the men.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186710280027"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> You said you could not swear to any one? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I said I could not swear to your knocking me down, but I can swear you picked the money up—there was a gaslight—I had had a glass of ale, bat wag not intoxicated.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18671028-name-164" type="witnessName">
